news.title: Avadi corporation ignores NGT fiat to evict lake encroachers in Tamil Nadu
news.para: The civic body has 12 lakes within its jurisdiction. The National Green Tribunal (NGT) last year had directed state authorities to identify and remove all encroachments on lakes to avoid flooding.

news.title: Corporators with dues miss e-auction notices in Bhopal
news.para: In some instances, properties are facing auction within 21-days for dues are no more than Rs 25,000. However, a property listed to a corporators, have yet to come under the e-auction hammer.

news.title: Mumbai: Housing societies unite against concrete units in Govandi
news.para: The Maharashtra Pollution Control Board (MPCB) served notices and closure directions to two plants and a show-cause notice to another last week stating why their application for grant of consent to operate should not be refused.

news.title: Residential sales in top seven cities up 68% year-on-year in 2022: Report
news.para: Bengaluru and Mumbai jointly led the annual sales in 2022 as they clocked more than 46,000 units (22% share each) followed by Delhi NCR at 38,000 units (18% share).

news.title: PE investments in Indian real estate touch $3.4 billion in 2022: Savills India
news.para: Savills India expects $3.5 billion - $4.0 billion of private equity investments in Indian real estate in 2023.

news.title: Unity Group, Parsvnath Developers to construct mall in Delhi
news.para: The agreement is part of the company's plan to double its retail portfolio and create a retail Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT).

news.title: DTCP nod to operate guesthouses in five prime sectors of Gurugram
news.para: According to the order by the office of DTCP director general, plot owners in five sectors — 26A, 27, 28, 42 and 43 — can apply for land-use change for operating guesthouses.

news.title: Supreme Universal inks pact to develop five-acre land parcel in Mumbai
news.para: The company has acquired the development rights of the said land parcel through its subsidiary Supreme Sky High LLP and will be investing nearly Rs 1,000 crore to develop the project.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to re-tender housing scheme 15 years after launch
news.para: The civic body has terminated the contract of Nirmithi Kendra, the implementing agency, at its risk and cost and decided to re tender the project.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body board hikes house tax by 10% from April 1
news.para: Sanjeev Sinha, chief tax assessment officer of GMC, said, "The house tax rate in Ghaziabad is one of the lowest in the state. So a proposal from our side was given to make it compatible with the circle rate, which was struck down by the board. The board, however, agreed to hike it by 10%, effective April 1, 2023."

news.title: YEIDA to hire consultant to manage building plans system
news.para: Officials said the system will automate the end-to-end process for building plan approvals—from empanelment of architects and online submission of documents and fees to issuance of occupation certificate.

news.title: Will file caveat in SC: Wave Group buyers after NCLAT order
news.para: Authority sources, however, said the developer may still apply for the restoration of the land and go for the reschedulement policy to clear dues and complete stalled projects.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA developing three more layouts for MIG
news.para: The VMRDA had to slash the price of the plots in its Palavalasa layout due to the poor response. The per square yard price was reduced to ₹14,500 from the earlier fixed ₹18,000 in the Palavalasa layout located near Anandapuram in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: KIIFB allots Rs 102 crore for land acquisition of Kochi metro phase II
news.para: Once the land acquisition is completed, Kochi Metro Rail Ltd (KMRL) will be able to initiate procedures for inviting tenders for construction of stations and Metro viaducts.

news.title: Complaint invalid if OC issued before RERA Act passed: Karnataka HC
news.para: The judge in the case pointed out that the project had lost its status as an ongoing project because the occupancy certificate had been issued prior to the act coming into effect. This means that the complainant, Shyama Shetty, cannot maintain a complaint against the developer, MS Provident Housing Limited, under the act.
